<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Nature and Animals</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
        }

        header {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2ecc71 0%, #27ae60 100%);
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 60px 20px;
        }

        header h1 {
            font-size: 3em;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }

        header p {
            font-size: 1.2em;
            opacity: 0.9;
        }

        nav {
            background-color: #27ae60;
            padding: 15px;
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            z-index: 100;
        }

        nav a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            margin: 0 20px;
            font-weight: 500;
            transition: opacity 0.3s;
        }

        nav a:hover {
            opacity: 0.8;
        }

        container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        section {
            margin: 40px 0;
            padding: 30px;
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        section h2 {
            color: #27ae60;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            font-size: 2em;
            border-bottom: 3px solid #2ecc71;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
        }

        section p {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            text-align: justify;
        }

        .animal-cards {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        .animal-card {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 8px;
            overflow: hidden;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            transition: transform 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
        }

        .animal-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
            box-shadow: 0 6px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
        }

        .animal-card-header {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2ecc71 0%, #27ae60 100%);
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 1.5em;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .animal-card-content {
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .animal-card-content p {
            font-size: 0.95em;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .animal-icon {
            font-size: 3em;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        footer {
            background-color: #27ae60;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
            margin-top: 50px;
        }

        .importance-list {
            background-color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-left: 4px solid #2ecc71;
            border-radius: 4px;
            margin: 15px 0;
        }

        .importance-list ul {
            margin-left: 20px;
        }

        .importance-list li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            header h1 {
                font-size: 2em;
            }

            nav a {
                display: block;
                margin: 10px 0;
            }

            section {
                padding: 20px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>🌍 Nature and Animals 🦁</h1>
        <p>Exploring the Beauty and Diversity of Our Natural World</p>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <a href="#nature">Nature</a>
        <a href="#animals">Animals</a>
        <a href="#importance">Importance</a>
        <a href="#conservation">Conservation</a>
    </nav>

    <container>
        <!-- Nature Section -->
        <section id="nature">
            <h2>🌿 Understanding Nature</h2>
            <p>
                Nature encompasses all the natural phenomena and living organisms that exist on Earth and beyond. 
                It includes forests, mountains, oceans, deserts, rivers, and the atmosphere. Nature is a complex 
                and interconnected system where every element plays a vital role in maintaining the balance of life.
            </p>
            <p>
                Our natural world is incredibly diverse, featuring thousands of ecosystems each with unique 
                characteristics. From the lush rainforests teeming with life to the vast savannas, deserts, and 
                cold tundras, nature demonstrates remarkable variety and adaptation. These environments are home 
                to countless species of plants, animals, insects, and microorganisms that have evolved over millions 
                of years to thrive in their specific habitats.
            </p>
            <p>
                The beauty of nature lies not only in its visual appeal but also in its intricate processes. 
                Photosynthesis, the water cycle, pollination, and decomposition are just a few of the remarkable 
                processes that keep our planet alive and thriving.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Animals Section -->
        <section id="animals">
            <h2>🦁 The Animal Kingdom</h2>
            <p>
                Animals are an essential part of Earth's biodiversity. They range from microscopic organisms to 
                the largest creatures ever to live on our planet. Animals have adapted to live in virtually every 
                environment, from the depths of the ocean to the highest mountains.
            </p>

            <div class="animal-cards">
                <div class="animal-card">
                    <div class="animal-card-header">
                        <div class="animal-icon">🦁</div>
                        Mammals
                    </div>
                    <div class="animal-card-content">
                        <p>
                            Mammals are warm-blooded vertebrates characterized by fur or hair, and the ability to 
                            nurse their young with milk. This group includes humans, whales, elephants, dogs, and bats.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="animal-card">
                    <div class="animal-card-header">
                        <div class="animal-icon">🦅</div>
                        Birds
                    </div>
                    <div class="animal-card-content">
                        <p>
                            Birds are feathered vertebrates adapted for flight. They lay eggs and have specialized 
                            respiratory systems. Birds play crucial roles as pollinators, seed dispersers, and pest controllers.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="animal-card">
                    <div class="animal-card-header">
                        <div class="animal-icon">🐠</div>
                        Fish
                    </div>
                    <div class="animal-card-content">
                        <p>
                            Fish are aquatic vertebrates with gills, fins, and scales. They inhabit oceans, rivers, and 
                            lakes. Fish are the most diverse group of vertebrates on Earth.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="animal-card">
                    <div class="animal-card-header">
                        <div class="animal-icon">🐢</div>
                        Reptiles
                    </div>
                    <div class="animal-card-content">
                        <p>
                            Reptiles are cold-blooded vertebrates covered in scales or plates. This group includes snakes, 
                            lizards, turtles, and crocodiles. Most lay eggs though some give live birth.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="animal-card">
                    <div class="animal-card-header">
                        <div class="animal-icon">🐸</div>
                        Amphibians
                    </div>
                    <div class="animal-card-content">
                        <p>
                            Amphibians can live both in water and on land. This group includes frogs, toads, salamanders, 
                            and newts. They play vital roles in ecosystems as predators and prey.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="animal-card">
                    <div class="animal-card-header">
                        <div class="animal-icon">🦗</div>
                        Insects
                    </div>
                    <div class="animal-card-content">
                        <p>
                            Insects are the most abundant animals on Earth. They have six legs, wings (in most species), 
                            and exoskeletons. Insects include beetles, butterflies, ants, and bees.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Importance Section -->
        <section id="importance">
            <h2>⭐ Importance of Nature and Animals</h2>
            <p>
                Nature and animals provide countless benefits to humanity and maintain the delicate balance of life on Earth.
            </p>
            <div class="importance-list">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Food Supply:</strong> Animals provide meat, fish, and dairy, while plants offer fruits, vegetables, and grains</li>
                    <li><strong>Oxygen Production:</strong> Plants and certain aquatic organisms produce the oxygen we breathe</li>
                    <li><strong>Climate Regulation:</strong> Forests and oceans absorb carbon dioxide and regulate global temperatures</li>
                    <li><strong>Medicine:</strong> Many pharmaceuticals are derived from natural compounds found in animals and plants</li>
                    <li><strong>Pollination:</strong> Bees, butterflies, and other insects pollinate crops and wild plants</li>
                    <li><strong>Water Purification:</strong> Wetlands and forests filter water naturally</li>
                    <li><strong>Soil Formation:</strong> Decomposers break down organic matter to create fertile soil</li>
                    <li><strong>Mental Health:</strong> Contact with nature reduces stress and improves overall well-being</li>
                    <li><strong>Cultural Value:</strong> Nature inspires art, literature, spirituality, and cultural traditions</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Conservation Section -->
        <section id="conservation">
            <h2>🌱 Conservation and Protection</h2>
            <p>
                Many species and ecosystems face threats from habitat loss, climate change, pollution, and overhunting. 
                Conservation efforts are critical to protect our natural world for future generations.
            </p>
            <div class="importance-list">
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Protected Areas:</strong> Establishing national parks and nature reserves preserves habitats</li>
                    <li><strong>Sustainable Practices:</strong> Using resources responsibly reduces environmental impact</li>
                    <li><strong>Renewable Energy:</strong> Transitioning to solar, wind, and hydroelectric power reduces pollution</li>
                    <li><strong>Reforestation:</strong> Planting trees helps restore ecosystems and combat climate change</li>
                    <li><strong>Education:</strong> Raising awareness about environmental issues encourages conservation</li>
                    <li><strong>Wildlife Protection Laws:</strong> Regulations prevent poaching and illegal trafficking of animals</li>
                    <li><strong>Pollution Reduction:</strong> Reducing plastic use and managing waste protects ecosystems</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <p style="margin-top: 20px;">
                Every individual can contribute to conservation by making conscious choices, supporting environmental 
                organizations, and advocating for policies that protect nature and animals.
            </p>
        </section>
    </container>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Nature and Animals. Dedicated to protecting our planet's biodiversity.</p>
        <p>Let's work together to preserve the beauty and wonder of nature for generations to come.</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
